Package: blosc
Title: Compress and Decompress Data Using the BLOSC Library
Version: 0.0.3.0001
Authors@R: 
    person("Pepijn", "de Vries", role = c("aut", "cre"),
      email = "pepijn.devries@outlook.com",
      comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-7961-6646"))
Description: Blosc is a blocking, shuffling and lossless compression
    algorithm. It is often used to compress n-dimensional structured
    array data. It is applied (amongst others) in the geo-spatial
    zarr file format. This package can be used to decompress such
    data or to compress data.
